volume.name: Shazam! and the Shazam Family! Annual

description:
Japan. The future. A new age of corporate feudalism. The worlds of business, organized crime, and politics now exist in a delicate interdependence. Enter the Noh, a government agency that secretly polices that balance of worlds.

Kabuki, an operative of the Noh, becomes deeply affected by the death of her mother and can only relate to the world through the security of a mask. She embarks on a quest to come to terms with her family, history, culture, and her mother's death... even if her personal crusade brings her in direct conflict with the powers she serves.

A mix of historical mythology, political intrigue, corporate espionage, and familial duty, elegantly told through the haunting lens of a child's fairy tale

The first chapter in one of the most critically acclaimed comics series of the nineites.

Contents

  • Fear the Reaper
  • Circle of Blood 1-6
  • An introduction by Jim Steranko
  • A glossary
  • An afterword by Takashi Hatrori & David Mack

Availability

this collection is/was available in one Hardcover signed edition and 4 trade editions (2-3 have nearly identical covers, just the color hue wavers a bit)
name: Circle of Blood

description:
By and by, we all grow up, and with the growing go the childhood stories, passed by like ciphers in the night. Gone the wide eyed wonder, the anticipation, the shrieking delight; let fly to the wind, the better to receive maturity. To be stable, to be somber; to work and be responsible, to set oneself to a life of order, and to do those which are the many things that grown-ups do.

Gone...

... but not lost.

There are those times, the moments known to all...
name: TPB
